Package org.javaToAvalla.model.terms

This package contains classes representing various terms used int the Java to AVALLA translation process.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AvallaCheckTerm
    Represents a check term in the Avalla language, which compares two terms: a left term and a right term.
    AvallaHeaderTerm
    Represents a header term in the Avalla language, which holds the name of a scenario.
    AvallaLoadTerm
    Represents a load term in the Avalla language, which is used to load an ASM (Abstract State Machine) specification.
    AvallaSetTerm
    Represents a set term in the Avalla language, which holds a name and a corresponding value.
    AvallaStepTerm
    Represents a step term in the Avalla framework, which triggers a step in the ASM (Abstract State Machine).
    AvallaTerm
    Represents the base class for all terms in the Avalla language.
    JavaArgumentTerm
    The Argument class represents a function argument with a name and an indicator of whether it is a primitive type or not.
    JavaAssertionTerm
    Represents a Java assertion term used to compare an actual value with an expected value in the Java context.
    JavaTerm
    Abstract class representing a generic Java term.
    JavaVariableTerm
    Represents a Java variable term, extending the JavaArgumentTerm class.
    Term
    Abstract class representing a generic term.

Package org.javaToAvalla.model.terms Description

This package contains classes representing various terms used int the Java to AVALLA translation process.

Classes included in this package:

  • Term - Abstract base class for all term types.
  • JavaTerm - Abstract class for Java-specific terms.
  • JavaVariableTerm - Represents a variable in Java.
  • JavaAssertionTerm - Represents an assertion in Java.
  • AvallaTerm - Abstract class for Avalla terms.
  • AvallaCheckTerm - Represents a check term in Avalla.
  • AvallaHeaderTerm - Represents a header term in Avalla.
  • AvallaLoadTerm - Represents a load term in Avalla.
  • AvallaSetTerm - Represents a set term in Avalla.
  • AvallaStepTerm - Represents a step command in Avalla.
